Freddie Gray , 25 , died on Sunday after he suffered a fatal spinal injury during an arrest in Baltimore  . 
  Baltimore police officials on Tuesday released the names of six officers involved in the arrest and the van transport of Gray  . 
  The Justice Department said it has opened a civil rights investigation into the death of Gray . 
  Hundreds of protestors took to the streets of Baltimore on Tuesday to protest the police force in Gray's name  . 
  Gray died after he 'had his spine 80 percent severed at his neck' during an April 12 arrest  . 
  The six officers have been suspended with pay pending an investigation . 
  Gray died a week after his arrest on April 12 . 
 